10.post_text: With BMW Gesture Control in the all-new BMW 7 Series, selected functions can be operated by means of defined hand movements. Simple gestures such as 'swiping' or 'pointing' are identified in the recognition area above the centre console and trigger a variety of functions such as accepting or rejecting an incoming telephone call. Volume can be adjusted by circular motions of the index finger. BMW Gesture Control complements the existing control systems such as the iDrive Touch Controller. Stay tuned to our Facebook page to find out more about the all-new BMW 7 Series. #drivingluxury

The BMW display key of the all-new BMW 7 Series shows a range of information about the vehicle's status and allows selected functions to be controlled via the integrated touch display. The time can be displayed, along with remaining fuel and current range, service notifications, as well as the current status of the central locking system, the windows and the glass roof. Stay tuned to our Facebook page to find out more about the all-new BMW 7 Series.
